                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "this kind of cmdline parsing is out of scope for `:nospecial`. It should be leveraging the existing parsing from `nvim_parse_cmd` (or whatever that uses internally)",
            "commit_id": "34b44e2ef7ddfdf81d62e0a4ee049a88b7ce67a4",
            "created_at": "2026-03-12T11:20:44Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -7100,6 +7099,60 @@ bool expr_map_locked(void)\n   return expr_map_lock > 0 && !(curbuf->b_flags & BF_DUMMY);\n }\n \n+/// \":nospecial {cmd} {arg}...\": execute an ex command with literal arguments.\n+/// bypass special character handling (|, \", %, etc).\n+static void ex_nospecial(exarg_T *eap)\n+{\n+  char *arg = skipwhite(eap->arg);\n+\n+  // find inner command name up to first space\n+  char *cmd_end = arg;\n+  while (*cmd_end != NUL && *cmd_end != ' ') {\n+    cmd_end++;\n+  }",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38114#discussion_r2923936704",
